text:
1 star is too generous.
Bought chicken, mutton and babat satay on Sat 30th Sept for supper.
Worst satay we ever tasted. Mutton was sour, babat was soggy. All the satay has NO spice.
Spent $141.00, what a waste of money. Will never recommend this seller to anyone.
Will feedback to Singapore Food Agency as well.
Not nice, i bought betawi, carrot cake and laksa. All not nice either too salty or doesnt taste like what it suppose to be. And its expensive, avg $8 per plate.
Order This from food panda. All the satay are sour. Cannot even eat them.
This stall should be given a 5 star Michelin adward for their authentic Malay Satay.

Both quality and quantity are of average standard. The prices are above nearby similar stalls. Good service.
